headlines.description: Keith Braxton had a triple double and Mark Flagg added a double double as St. Francis (Pa.) pulled away late to beat Fairleigh Dickinson 74-60 in Northeast Conference play on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Braxton has triple double to lead St. Francis (PA) to win

headlines.description: Desonta Bradford had career highs of 31 points and five 3-pointers and East Tennessee State remained unbeaten in the Southern Conference with a 96-76 victory over Samford on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bradford has career-high 31 in ETSU's 96-76 victory

headlines.description: Bryson Scott scored 23 points, John Konchar 21 and Kason Harrell 20 as Fort Wayne defeated Oral Roberts 85-75 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: 3 score 20, Fort Wayne tops Oral Roberts 85-75

headlines.description: MaCio Teague hit seven 3-pointers and scored a career-high 36 points to help UNC Asheville pick up a win at Campbell, 64-57 on Thursday night to maintain a share of the Big South Conference lead with Radford.
headlines.shortLinkText: UNC Asheville shares Big South lead, beats Campbell 64-57

headlines.description: Scottie James had 21 points and Caleb Homesley added 16 as Liberty rolled over Winthrop 77-61 on Thursday night to sweep the Eagles for the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: James leads Liberty to 77-61 win as Flames sweep Winthrop

headlines.description: Devin Sibley scored 21 points and Furman shot 51 percent from the field to beat Mercer 85-73 on Thursday night.
D'Marcus Simonds had 21 points, nine rebounds and six assists as Georgia State got past Arkansas State 77-66 on Thursday night for its eighth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simonds leads Georgia St. to 8th straight win, 77-66

headlines.description: Averyl Ugba scored 28 points with a career-high 17 rebounds, including 4 points in the final 28 seconds, and Austin Peay held on to beat UT Martin 59-57 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ugba's big night helps Governors outlast Skyhawks

headlines.description: Jerrick Harding and Dusty Baker each scored 21 points and Weber State extended its winning streak to four with a 90-80 win at Southern Utah on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Weber State wins 4th straight, beats Southern Utah 90-80

headlines.description: Demario Beck made a layup at the buzzer to lift Coastal Carolina to a 56-54 overtime victory over Texas State on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beck's OT layup gets Coastal Carolina past Texas State 56-54

headlines.description: Brayon Blake scored 28 points with eight rebounds, Victor Sanders added 22 points with seven assists and Idaho turned back Portland State 97-88 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blake, Sanders combined for 50, Idaho tops Portland St 97-88

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
